The paper presents a machine learning technique for large-scale data analytics, which involves the use of stochastic configuration networks (SCNs) as base learner models and negative correlation learning (NCL) strategy for evaluating output weights. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of iterative methods for evaluating output weights based on heterogeneous features, which suggests that it may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NE) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of ensemble learning techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
